This Google Earth project offers an extensive mapping of North Korea's economic, cultural, political, and military infrastructures. Through the topic menu, users of this program have easy access to geographical information on North Korea's agriculture projects, aviation facilities, communications, hospitals, hotels, energy infrastructure, financial services, leisure destinations, manufacturing facilities, markets, mines, religious locations, restaurants, schools, and transportation infrastructure. In addition to locations of economic interest, this map also displays anti-aircraft locations, the Demilitarized Zone (DMZ) and Northern Line Limit Line (NLL), incarceration facilities, political monuments, political residencies, military bases, and nuclear facilities.

properties.name: Sariwon Canal
properties.description:
KCNA-2007
Canal Tells President's Warm Love for People
   Pyongyang, September 14 (KCNA) -- There is a canal flowing through Sariwon, seat of North Hwanghae Province. 
    The Sariwon Canal which adds beauty to the scenery of the city and caters to the cultural and emotional life of the citizens conveys the devoted efforts made by President Kim Il Sung for the people in his lifetime. 
    The President visited the city in February Juche 43 (1954) and indicated the orientation and way for constructing a canal running through the heart of the city.
    Indeed, this is a good plan no one had conceived for the formation and construction of the city. 
    The citizens of Sariwon turned out in the canal project as one, upholding the President's plan associated with his constant view and motto "The people are my God".
    After the completion of the project, the President called at the city again and saw with great satisfaction the canal in which clean water flew. 
    The Sariwon Canal was thus built thanks to the warm affection of the President for the people.

properties.name: Taehung Fishing Enterprise
properties.description:
http://www.kcckp.net/en/periodic/korea/index.php?contents+2314+2008-09+80+8

The Kim Chaek Taehung Fishing Enterprise in North Hamgyong Province is a leading fishing base. 

The enterprise has a long wharf, large and small trawlers, an unloading place shaded by a gull-shaped roof, the streamlined fish-processing workshop and the ship repair workshop. 

It is equipped with refrigerating flow line, quick refrigerating room, scales-removing machine, vacuum disemboweling and cutting machines, cycloid tube sealing machine, high-pressure sterilizing oven and packing facilities. 

Fully aware of their responsibility for the peoples diet, the officials and employees in the enterprise introduce different halieutics to increase the catch of fishes in the vast fishing ground. 

They carefully plan fishing operations according to season and catch fishes in time. 

The ship repair workshop with accessory processing facilities solves the problems arising in repairing ships to increase their operation rates. 

The enterprise introduces advanced cultivation methods to increase the output of aquatic products. 

The combined farms raise kelp, scallop, sea cucumber, ear shell and the like and the processing workshop ensures the high rate of freshness of fishes and strictly observes standard technical regulations corresponding to the processes to upgrade the quality of products. 

The enterprise produces refrigerated, salted, dried and canned products. 

The officials and employees strive to carry out the tasks given by the leader Kim Jong Il on his visit to their enterprise in May.
